Components.Specifications.Presentation

Class CPresentationComp

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.awt.Component
      • java.awt.Container

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    INodeObject, IPAMOJAComponent, IPresentationComp, java.awt.image.ImageObserver, java.awt.MenuContainer, java.beans.PropertyChangeListener, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener

    public class CPresentationComp
extends CPAMOJAComponent
implements IPresentationComp, INodeObject, java.io.Serializable, java.beans.PropertyChangeListener
    A composite component containing facilities for customizing the presentation style of program text to user's preferences. It is composed of a Patterns component and a SymbolStyleCustomizer component. Presentation component is observer/observable. It observes a Language component and maintains consistency between its own valid symbol domain and the symbols of the lexical-part of a language. It notifies its observers of changes in the layout specifications and changes in its symbol categories as well as their color and font attributes.
    See Also:
    CPatternsComp, CSymbolStyleCustomizerComp, CLanguageComp, Serialized Form
